<DOC><DOCNO> AP891111-0043 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-11-89 0647EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BRF--NightStalker     11-11 0151</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Night Stalker,0154</SECOND><HEAD>`Night Stalker' Loses Jail Privileges For Shower Rampage</HEAD><DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Jailers prohibited convicted ``NightStalker'' Richard Ramirez from watching TV or receiving visitorsfor 10 days for vandalizing a ceiling air vent while taking ashower.   The incident Thursday at the Men's Central Jail was notconsidered an attempted jailbreak, sheriff's Deputy GeorgeDucoulombier said Friday.   Ramirez, 29, was placed in ``administrative segregation'' at thejail after he pulled the cover off an air vent while showeringalone, sheriff's Sgt. Ernie Roop said.   The self-described devil worshipper was sentenced to death onTuesday. He was being held at the county-run jail while awaitingtransfer to San Quentin State Prison.   Ramirez was convicted of 13 murders and 30 other felony chargesstemming from a string of murders, rapes and burglaries. As withall death sentences, Ramirez's case will automatically be appealedto the state Supreme Court.</TEXT></DOC>